# Translation & billing tier scope (InterpreterAI)

## Final Boss 2 (named snapshot — OpenAI interpreter only)

- **Final Boss 2** is the product label for the **current OpenAI interpreter stack**: same `/translate` pipeline and client behavior used for **Platinum**, **`unlimited`**, **Basic/Professional** OpenAI `plan_type` values (e.g. `basic`, `basic-openai`, `professional`, `professional-openai`), **`platinum`**, and **OpenAI trial tiers** (`trial`, `trial-openai`) when requests use the OpenAI path (i.e. not `useMachineTranslation`).
- **Git:** frozen reference **`final-boss-2`** (annotated tag on the tree that shipped this baseline).
- **Libre / machine line is not Final Boss 2:** tiers that use **`useMachineTranslation`** (`trial-libre`, `basic-libre`, `professional-libre`, `platinum-libre`) keep their **own** baseline — do not relabel or merge them into FB2; leave those files and behaviors as-is unless a task explicitly targets Libre only.

## Do not change (Final Boss 2 / OpenAI)

- **Platinum** and **`unlimited`** translation, prompts, finalize behavior, retries, or client paths tied to those plans.
- **OpenAI trial tiers:** default **`trial`** and **`trial-openai`** (same OpenAI `/translate` stack as Platinum). Do not modify their behavior, prompts, or shared OpenAI-only code paths except to fix unrelated bugs with explicit user approval.

## Allowed to change (Libre / machine translation only)

- **`trial-libre`**, **`basic-libre`**, **`professional-libre`**, and **`platinum-libre`** **machine path** only: server Libre path (`useMachineTranslation` in `transcription.ts`), `basic-pro-translate.ts`, `libretranslate.ts`. **Client translation dispatch must stay identical to Platinum** — engine swap is server-side only.

## Implementation discipline

- When editing shared files (e.g. `transcription.ts`), **gate** new behavior with `useMachineTranslation` (or equivalent) so **Platinum and OpenAI trials stay unchanged** unless the user explicitly asks otherwise. **Do not** add Basic/Professional-only branches in `use-transcription.ts` — same client flow for all plans.
- After completing requested work, **commit and push** to `main` unless the user says not to.
